    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1401" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀρείων, ἄρειον</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀρ</span>, cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄριστος,
            ἀρετή</span>): comp. (answering to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγαθός</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">better, superior</span>, etc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλέονες καὶ ἀρείους</span>, ‘mightier,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 9.48</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; πρότερος καὶ ἀρείων,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 23.588</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            κρεῖσσον καὶ ἄρειον</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            6.182</span></i>; (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παῖδες</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οἱ πλέονες κακίους, παῦροι δέ τε πατρὸς
            ἀρείους</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.277</span></i>; adv.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τάχα δὲ φράσεται καὶ ἄρειον</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 23.114</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
